  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two concentric loops of wire. The inner wire has a radius of R sub 1 and carries a clockwise current of I sub 0, and the outer wire has a radius of R sub 2 and carries no current through it.\" src=\"/images/48fe494a9447a7a7f73f8420fa7137a3.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A loop of conducting wire has a clockwise current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I sub 0\"><math alttext=\"I sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>. A larger conductive loop is placed concentric with the smaller loop and does not have a current. The current in the smaller, inner loop is gradually reduced to zero. When the smaller loop has a current of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction I sub 0 over 3\"><math alttext=\"the fraction I sub 0 over 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></span></span> the value of the current in the larger, outer loop is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I sub 2\"><math alttext=\"I sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>. Which of the following statements correctly indicates if the value of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I sub 2\"><math alttext=\"I sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> can be determined, and provides appropriate justification?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
